<title type="html"><![CDATA[Bad Music on Yobo FamiClone, Fixable? How to Work Around?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7606&amp;p=76073#p76073"><![CDATA[
I'm not aware of any possible way of fixing it since the Clone chip is already made with the error. Now provided you could reprogram a cartridge you could swap the duty cycles in the software so that it sounds right on the messed up clone and wrong on the authentic hardware. <br /><br />In theory homebrew could have an option to allow for swapping duty cycles so if played on a clone system it would still sound correct if the user enabled the swap. <br /><br />The best solution is to just use authentic hardware. Leave the cheap clones to people that don't know better.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Fri Apr 01, 2011 2:57 pm</p><hr />
